# API Conventions

## REST Style

- Use nouns for resources: `/api/analyze/photo`, `/api/history`.
- Use HTTP methods correctly: GET (read), POST (create/action), PUT/PATCH (update).
- Return appropriate status codes: 200, 201, 400, 401, 404, 500.

## Response Format

```typescript
// Success
{ data: { redFlags: string[] } }
{ data: { id: string, identifier: string, createdAt: string } }

// Error
{ error: { message: string, code?: string } }
```

## Validation

- Validate all user input (body, params, query).
- Return 400 with clear error message for validation failures.
- Sanitize file uploads: type, size, content.

## CORS

- Configure CORS for frontend origin only in production.
- Allow credentials if using cookies/sessions.

## Rate Limiting

- Consider rate limiting for `/api/analyze/*` to protect AI costs.
- Return 429 when limit exceeded.
